In this article, President Obama reflects on his visit with the families of the victims of the Orlando shooting. He reassures them that they are not alone and that the American people stand with them. He emphasizes the importance of speaking up about issues such as gun violence and tolerance to create a safer and more loving world for our children. President Obama also discusses the ongoing efforts to stop attacks like these and destroy ISIL. He calls for stricter gun control measures to prevent future tragedies. Additionally, he talks about the responsibility of parents to teach their children about love, acceptance, and the importance of helping others. The article concludes with President Obama wishing all fathers a happy Father's Day and urging everyone to be present for each other and show love and support.